title: SHWF visits Kowloon City District
content_text:
p>The Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food, Dr York Chow, this afternoon (April 
26), visited Kowloon City District to update himself on the latest developments 
in health, welfare and environmental hygiene issues under his portfolio.  Accompanied by District Officer (Kowloon City), Mr Kevin Yeung, and District 
Social Welfare Officer (Kowloon City), Mrs Barbara Lai, Dr Chow arrived at the 
Kowloon City Integrated Family Service Centre and Social Security Field Unit of 
the Social Welfare Department at Ma Hang Chung Road to look at their daily

the Social Welfare Department at Ma Hang Chung Road to look at their daily 
operations.  Dr Chow met members of a volunteer group for single parents in the centre. 
Members shared with Dr Chow their experience in volunteer work, saying that this 
had helped them build up a social network, whereby they could share among 
themselves their problems and engender a sense of mutual support.  Dr Chow inspected some environmental black spots at the rear lanes of Hau Wong 
Road where a dozen licensed food establishments are located. During the

Road where a dozen licensed food establishments are located. During the 
inspection, he was briefed on the cleaning and blitz operations carried out by 
the Food and Environmental Hygiene Department.  He was pleased to see that there had been improvements in the environment in the 
locality as a result of the joint efforts by government departments and the 
community.  Dr Chow also took time to tour the Kowloon Walled City Park.  During today's district visit, Dr Chow met local representatives including the

chairman of the Kowloon City District Council, Mr Wong Kwok-keung, and 
vice-chairman, Mr Chan Ka-wai, to exchange views on various issues in the 
district.  Ends/Tuesday, April 26, 2005
